<title>COTE D'IVOIRE: Ivorian commodity marketing board changes detailed.</title>
<headline>Ivorian commodity marketing board changes detailed.</headline>
<dateline>ABIDJAN 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ivory Coast's commodities marketing board has appointed new staff to key positions and created new posts covering exports, quality, processing and auditing, Caistab and donor sources said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The reshuffle follows the appointment in late 1996 of a new Caistab managing director, Yves-Marie Koissy.</p>
<p>Donors, exporters and industry buyers have since expressed concerns over cocoa and coffee quality, export contract auction rules and Caistab running costs.</p>
<p>Ivory Coast is holding two weeks of talks with donors until May 9 aimed at resolving differences over reforms linked to a $150 million World Bank agriculture loan.</p>
<p>An updated list of key Casitab staff follows. Asterisks denote new posts:</p>
<p>Commercial desk:</p>
<p>    Interim Commercial Director	- Lambert N'Guessan,</p>
<p>*Deputy Sales Dir. (cocoa/coffee) - Moussa Claude Kone</p>
<p>    Coffee desk director		 - Mathile Kouassi</p>
<p>    Cocoa desk director		  - unnamed</p>
<p>   *Deputy shipping (loading) dir.   - unnamed</p>
<p>*Cocoa and coffee export director - Amouan Acquah</p>
<p>   *Bill recovery service		- Kouame Comoe</p>
<p>   *Statistics service		   - Yedo Nomel</p>
<p>Technical department:</p>
<p>    Technical Manager		    - Yapo Atsepy</p>
<p>    Deputy				   - Amany Assie</p>
<p>    Forecasting			    - Alexandre Lamizana</p>
<p>   *Factories				- Lea Yapobi</p>
<p>   *Quality Control			- Georges Koffi Amani</p>
<p>Financial:</p>
<p>    Technical Director		   - Edouard N'Guessan</p>
<p>    Accounting			     - Leopold Djikaou</p>
<p>Management:</p>
<p>    Cabinet Director		     - Dagobert Banzio</p>
<p>   *Audit and Control		    - Avi Adro</p>
<p>   *Interim Commercial Director	- Lambert N'Guessan</p>
<p>   *Inspectors			     - Atse Kouassi, Niango</p>
<p>						   Damase</p>
<p>Caistab managing director Yves-Marie Koissy, appointed in late 1996, was not in Ivory Coast this week and so was unavailable for comment.</p>
<p>-- Matthew Bunce, Abidjan newsroom +225 21 90 90</p>
